<p>These are entirely different concepts than the stated assumption that most people spend their income, the conclusion from that being it won&#8217;t matter too much in which end you choose to tax it.</p>
<p>I believe you are describing the problem with flat taxation to a high and accurate degree, which is also why I argued for a compensatory mechanism to offset this problem. The citizen&#8217;s salary would not only solve that problem, but other problems too.</p>
