May 19, 2011 - 11:59</a> </div>
<p><i>then you just need to match an individual to an address at one single point to get a complete history of his or her transactions</i></p>
<p>This problem is addressed within the Bitcoin infrastructure. Every transaction is received at a <b>new and unique</b> address. Only you hold your collection of addresses.</p>
