<p>Given enough resources, anything can be traced &#8211; or at least guesstimated with a good enough degree of accuracy.</p>
<p>But the amount of effort required is vast though. If everyone using Bitcoin or other cryptocurrency has to be approached with the same type of effort which went into finding Osama Bin Laden then you can safely say that spending a million in order to retrieve ten thousand bucks in back taxes never will be a winning model.</p>
