<p>You are not unusual but human beings are not designed that way. We have to work, play, hunt. Without being a useful member of a group we cant exist. You would certainly become a great artist, open source software engineer, gardener or anything else you are passionate about. You would enjoy and the society would become better for it, not worse. Check out &#8220;Voyage from yesteryear&#8221; or Ursula Le Guin book &#8220;Dispossessed&#8221; for more detailed descriptions and ideas about such.</p>
