May 19, 2011 - 13:36</a> </div>
<p>Very interesting.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m not entirely sure whether this proposal will solve the problem, however. After all, if payments can be made without notice, then sales can be, as well. Sure, if someone is doing business out in the open, you can try to make sure they pay their VAT. And that would help make sure everyone up in the sales chain pays, as well. But that will still leave e.g. purely virtual businesses untouched.</p>
<p>Of course, it&#8217;s still better than not collecting taxes at all.</p>
