<p>I am not a big fan of everything Milton Friedman said, but here is one thing he said that seems relevant to this topic:</p>
<p>&#8220;In my opinion, the least bad tax is the property tax on the unimproved value of land, the Henry George argument of many, many years ago.&#8221; &#8211; Milton Friedman</p>
