<p>You are missing the point. Rick is talking about a form of currency which will invalidate any and all old models of fiscal calculation in one go if it is ever adopted. Since the payoff of adopting it are going to be a 30-50% effective revenue increase for both companies and employers it&#8217;s just a matter of time before cryptocurrency becomes an established standard.</p>
<p>Rick is simply putting up an analysis of the ramifications, and it&#8217;s a fairly solid one. Once cryptocurrency becomes a norm, income taxation will, to all effects, become voluntary. You can bemoan that fact as you will, but the fact is you are simply shooting the messenger and clapping your hands over your ears.</p>
